    "display_name": "Cohesive Flourishing Framework (CFF) v7.3",
    "analysis_variants": {
      "default": {
        "description": "Sequential social cohesion analysis with chain-of-thought methodology and tension mathematics",
        "analysis_prompt": "You are an expert discourse analyst specializing in social cohesion and rhetorical strategy analysis. Analyze this text through focused sequential steps, examining each dimension group independently before integration.\n\nSTEP 1 - IDENTITY AXIS ANALYSIS\nFocus ONLY on tribal dominance vs. individual dignity patterns:\n- Score tribal dominance (0.0-1.0) with textual evidence.\n- Score individual dignity (0.0-1.0) with textual evidence.\n- Assess salience for each (0.0-1.0): How central is the appeal?\n- State confidence for each (0.0-1.0): How certain are you?\nShow your work.\n\nSTEP 2 - EMOTIONAL CLIMATE AXIS ANALYSIS\nNow focus ONLY on fear vs. hope patterns:\n- Score fear (0.0-1.0) with textual evidence.\n- Score hope (0.0-1.0) with textual evidence.\n- Assess salience for each (0.0-1.0).\n- State confidence for each (0.0-1.0).\nShow your work.\n\nSTEP 3 - SUCCESS ORIENTATION AXIS ANALYSIS\nNow focus ONLY on envy vs. compersion patterns:\n- Score envy (0.0-1.0) with textual evidence.\n- Score compersion (0.0-1.0) with textual evidence.\n- Assess salience for each (0.0-1.0).\n- State confidence for each (0.0-1.0).\nShow your work.\n\nSTEP 4 - RELATIONAL CLIMATE AXIS ANALYSIS\nNow focus ONLY on enmity vs. amity patterns:\n- Score enmity (0.0-1.0) with textual evidence.\n- Score amity (0.0-1.0) with textual evidence.\n- Assess salience for each (0.0-1.0).\n- State confidence for each (0.0-1.0).\nShow your work.\n\nSTEP 5 - GOAL ORIENTATION AXIS ANALYSIS\nNow focus ONLY on fragmentative vs. cohesive goals patterns:\n- Score fragmentative goals (0.0-1.0) with textual evidence.\n- Score cohesive goals (0.0-1.0) with textual evidence.\n- Assess salience for each (0.0-1.0).\n- State confidence for each (0.0-1.0).\nShow your work.\n\nFINAL STEP - INTEGRATION\nReview your analysis and provide the final structured output."
      }
    },
